{"id":719910,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/B._V._Doshi","text":"Balkrishna Vithaldas Doshi, OAL, (born 26 August 1927) is an Indian architect. His best known designs are IIM Bangalore, IIM Udaipur, NIFT Delhi, Amdavad ni Gufa, CEPT University, and the Aranya Low Cost Housing development in Indore.\nIn 2018, he became the first Indian architect to receive the Pritzker Prize. He was also awarded the Padma Shri.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Ordre_des_Arts_et_des_Lettres","surface_form":"OAL","offset":28},{"uri":"Architect","surface_form":"architect","offset":68},{"uri":"Indian_Institute_of_Management_Bangalore","surface_form":"IIM Bangalore","offset":106},{"uri":"Indian_Institute_of_Management_Udaipur","surface_form":"IIM Udaipur","offset":121},{"uri":"National_Institute_of_Fashion_Technology","surface_form":"NIFT Delhi","offset":134},{"uri":"Amdavad_ni_Gufa","surface_form":"Amdavad ni Gufa","offset":146},{"uri":"CEPT_University","surface_form":"CEPT University","offset":163},{"uri":"Indore","surface_form":"Indore","offset":227},{"uri":"Indian_people","surface_form":"Indian","offset":264},{"uri":"Pritzker_Prize","surface_form":"Pritzker Prize","offset":296},{"uri":"Padma_Shri","surface_form":"Padma Shri","offset":336}]}